***Kazuya Terashima*** 寺嶋 一弥 (October 13, 1958 – October 6, 2020), known by his pen name ***Izumi Matsumoto*** まつもと泉, was a Japanese manga artist best known for ***Kimagure Orange Road***. His career started in 1982, publishing his comic ***Milk Report*** in the manga magazine ***Weekly Shōnen Jump***. But real success came in 1984, publishing ***Kimagure Orange Road*** in the same magazine. He revealed that he was afflicted with a cerebrospinal fluid disease (stemming from a car accident when he was three years old) that forced him to take six years off work, and he hoped to bring attention to this disorder through his manga. On November 3, 2019, Terashima revealed that he had been diagnosed with spinal stenosis. Matsumoto died at 61 on October 6, 2020.

* The Bleach Beat Collections is a set of CDs published by Sony Music featuring recordings by the original Japanese voice actors that provide a look at the personalities of the characters they play, as well as the voice actors themselves. The first CD was released on June 22, 2005, and twenty-one volumes followed across four named sets called Sessions.

* A number of additional collections have been released. Two volumes were released as "The Best", with each volume containing twenty-four songs each on two discs; the first volume was released on March 21, 2007, and the second one on March 18, 2009. 

 * The "Bleach Breathless Collection" contains six releases featuring five tracks of the individual Soul Reaper. An audio quality comparison upload for those interested on the Latin Spanish dub. Spoiler: ANICOM's audio quality sounds far better.

The LACRA release is complete and available on Nyaa, while ANICOM is an ongoing project and it'll still take some time to get all 291. ANICOM uses the 30A as their video source so if you thought about watching it with the Dbox, you'll need to sync it.

ANICOM will release HQ audio releases of Dragon Ball Z and then (hopefully) Dragon Ball GT as these two are available, though Dragon Ball is a bit of a rarity. It sure is nice to hear the Latin Spanish dub in high quality than some compressed shit.

***Every of my torrent comes from original CDs that I have bought (or that my friends lent me). If you check my torrents and you don’t find an artist or anime you are looking for, it means that nether I or my friends have those CDs. I don’t create discographies on commission, I’m sorry. If you find any other errors or oversights, please let me know. They will be corrected at the next torrent’s update. Thank you for your collaboration.***

Ver. [2021.10.08]
- [2021.01.27] 田所あずさ｜Waver ***fixed an issue with the album cover***

Ver. [2021.02.12]
- [2021.01.27] 田所あずさ｜Waver ***new album***

Ver. [2020.12.31]
- [2020.11.11] 田所あずさ｜ヤサシイセカイ

Sometimes, a seiyuu releases such a number of CDs during her career that it may be difficult not to get lost. Therefore, for this collection (and possibly also for the next ones) I wanted to try something different: I decided to divide the CDs labelling them into “Eras”. Musically speaking, an “Era” is composed of all single CDs that precede the release of an album or mini-album (which, usually, includes some or all of the songs included in these singles). When the album is released, an Era ends and a new one begins starting from the next single. Every Era is named after the title of the album that concludes it and, normally, gathers songs that are not present in previous Eras, nor will be in future ones. In this case, Azusa’s discography is indeed divided into four Eras, one for each of her albums.

description:
This is a complete (as to my knowledge) collection of the Eurobeat Flash albums.
Senzlord mentioned that my original collection was missing some files. I looked for a complete version around the time of the original comment, but I did not find one. I checked my old uploads again for comments, and I decided to search again, and did manage to find a complete version of the Flash series. My original upload (https://nyaa.si/view/1088485) contained some album art for the albums, so I added those to the corresponding albums in this new upload, but only about 1/4 of the albums have them.
If anyone has some definitive list of Eurobeat releases and knows what other ones might be missing, I will try to see if I can find them and upload them individually.
I wish there was some sort of notification for messages here so we could at least be able to see responses somewhat promptly, as this is probably 5 months after seeing the complaint to actually addressing it, but it is what it is.
Check my previous uploads for other soundtracks or uploads as there are plenty more.

title: [AV1+Opus+AAC] スーパーマリオワールドで、ウエスタンショー / Western Show + Super Mario Hyadain + HD
files: Super Mario Hyadain HD (1M Sub Special).mkv
Super Mario Hyadain HD vs Original Comparison.mkv
スーパーマリオワールドで、ウエスタンショー .mka
description:
The [HD remake](https://youtu.be/7EbBIPd5Kuc) & [comparison video](https://youtu.be/R_DBxGy4xcs) was downloaded using yt-dlp for formats: 140, 251 and 399. They were then muxxed together.

[Original audio](https://youtu.be/m5hQpND9Xao) was also downloaded off youtube with yt-dlp but with track 134 instead of 399 for the video. I then took a screenshot of one of the frames using MPC-HC and optimised the png to attach it as cover art.

### Flash animation
I downloaded it off [Newgrounds]() using the internet archive then rendered it using [swivel](https://www.newgrounds.com/wiki/creator-resources/flash-resources/swivel).

Audio was left untouched from the youtube (using the audio from the "HD remake") and the original MP3 from the swf animation.

Video was encoded using aomenc with the following settings:
`--bit-depth=10 --cpu-used=4 --end-usage=q --cq-level=30 --threads=4 --lag-in-frames=48 --enable-keyframe-filtering=2 --enable-obmc=1 --enable-cdef=1 --arnr-maxframes=15 --arnr-strength=6 --enable-fwd-kf=1 --quant-b-adapt=1 --enable-chroma-deltaq=1 --tile-rows=1 --tile-columns=2`

Video res is 3840x2414p20 (it's such a weird resolution because I removed the 4:3 letterboxing from the top of the video (I left the bottom because it contained the subtitles).

![Cover](https://i.postimg.cc/zfCF57PL/Cover.jpg) 
Artist：Crazy Ken Band
Release time:\xa02021.9.8
Publisher：Universal Music LLC

2021年デビュー40周年を迎える横山が、そのエネルギーの源でもある自身のバンド“クレイジーケンバンド”のルーツを示すカヴァー・アルバムをリリース。今作はまさに横山が駆け抜けた70`s~90`sにかけてのジャパニーズサウンドの隅から隅まで、とにかく横山が好きで好きでたまらない曲のみをカヴァー。まさにこれこそがクレイジーケンバンドの真骨頂であるジャンルレスな音楽の源だ。収録曲には「空港」(74年)や、「ルビーの指環」(81年)、「接吻-kiss-」(93年)などの70年代から90年代にかけての誰もが知るヒット曲の他、「よこはま・たそがれ」(71年)、「時間よ止まれ」(78年)、「雨に泣いてる」(78年)、「あまい囁き」(73年)等、予想以上にジャンレスな選曲となっている。また女性ボーカル曲を歌う横山や、メンバーのスモーキー・テツニやAyesha(アイシャ)がリードをとる曲もあり、クレイジーケンバンドだからできるカヴァー・アルバムが完成した。

title: [丸子家族][春之歌(Haru no Uta)]樱桃子未发表毕业歌[独唱版+合唱版][WebRip][GB+BIG5][1080P][MP4]
description:
![][0]

在这首歌中，樱桃子怀着对那一人生阶段的珍惜以及庆祝的情怀，在毕业典礼和毕业季上为这首被大家传唱的歌曲作词。由AKB48参与了「重播（ヘビーローテーション）」等歌曲制作的山崎燿作曲，以及其他歌手一起在2015年完成了这首歌。

虽然当时没有发行，但饱含温柔和温暖的歌曲，在相关人员心中留下了深刻的印象。

为了阻止去年的新型冠状病毒传播，毕业典礼规模被缩小，而后停办。为了向更多人展示毕业典礼的气氛，官方与NHK特别节目「大家的毕业典礼（みんなの卒業式）」合作，参加了【LINE#大家的毕业典礼】策划。

在限定公布期间，粉丝们纷纷前来询问。

樱桃子在制作期间表示："我一直想尝试为毕业典礼歌唱。如果这首歌能成为大家的必唱歌曲..."。通过这首歌在毕业典礼的时刻表达了对学校是思念以及感激之情。
